00:01:34,940 --> 00:01:36,940
[Second Chance Romance]

18
00:01:37,020 --> 00:01:39,940
[Episode 2]

19
00:01:40,260 --> 00:01:40,620
Siting,

20
00:01:41,180 --> 00:01:42,060
your second audition is tomorrow.

21
00:01:43,860 --> 00:01:45,220
I hope I make it through.

22
00:01:45,620 --> 00:01:46,780
If you get in,

23
00:01:46,860 --> 00:01:48,100
will you go abroad for further training?

24
00:01:48,260 --> 00:01:49,900
Who knows if I'll even pass?

25
00:01:49,980 --> 00:01:50,980
You'll definitely get in.

26
00:01:51,980 --> 00:01:52,980
You always know what to say.

27
00:01:53,540 --> 00:01:53,860
Here.

28
00:01:54,420 --> 00:01:55,260
Did I tell you?

29
00:01:55,620 --> 00:01:57,220
Zeyuan earned money
by writing code for someone.

30
00:01:57,620 --> 00:01:58,580
He said once he gets paid,

31
00:01:58,740 --> 00:01:59,700
he's treating us to a big meal.

32
00:01:59,940 --> 00:02:00,940
That's amazing.

33
00:02:01,340 --> 00:02:02,340
Then I'd better start thinking

34
00:02:02,340 --> 00:02:03,740
about how to make that meal count.

35
00:02:03,740 --> 00:02:04,420
Totally okay.

36
00:02:04,620 --> 00:02:05,540
I don't know

37
00:02:05,780 --> 00:02:07,780
what my mom ate
when she was pregnant with him.

38
00:02:07,780 --> 00:02:09,460
How come he's so much smarter than me?

39
00:02:10,020 --> 00:02:11,260
So hardworking and driven.

40
00:02:11,700 --> 00:02:12,940
Top of everything you do, right?

41
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:14,540
Wang Shuhan, that's enough.

42
00:02:15,500 --> 00:02:16,420
Did you forget why we're here today?

43
00:02:17,300 --> 00:02:18,380
Alright, I'll stop.

44
00:02:19,340 --> 00:02:20,500
Siting, we came specifically

45
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:21,940
to cheer you on today.

46
00:02:22,060 --> 00:02:22,340
Right.

47
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:23,980
Let's use this as a toast.

48
00:02:24,220 --> 00:02:25,700
To your success tomorrow

49
00:02:25,780 --> 00:02:26,540
and getting into Queen Ballet.

50
00:02:26,700 --> 00:02:27,780
- Go for it!
- Go for it!

51
00:02:33,860 --> 00:02:34,940
I don't know.

52
00:02:36,020 --> 00:02:36,940
Her shoes.

53
00:02:37,140 --> 00:02:38,260
I don't know what's going on.

54
00:02:50,820 --> 00:02:52,140
Something's wrong with the shoes.

55
00:02:52,780 --> 00:02:53,420
What do you think?

56
00:03:06,100 --> 00:03:07,300
Hello, do you have a reservation?

57
00:03:07,460 --> 00:03:07,940
Table one.

58
00:03:08,020 --> 00:03:08,620
Right this way, please.

59
00:03:09,140 --> 00:03:10,700
Alright. You're about to burst.

60
00:03:12,060 --> 00:03:12,780
Please, come in.

61
00:03:19,580 --> 00:03:20,980
Tan Siting!

62
00:03:22,020 --> 00:03:23,260
I've missed you so much.

63
00:03:23,260 --> 00:03:25,140
After all these years,
you're finally back.

64
00:03:25,260 --> 00:03:27,180
Why didn't you call me
the second you landed?

65
00:03:27,180 --> 00:03:28,940
If I'd called you
the moment I got off the plane,

66
00:03:28,940 --> 00:03:29,780
would you have even answered?

67
00:03:29,780 --> 00:03:30,740
Fine. Let me get a good look at you.

68
00:03:30,740 --> 00:03:31,220
Let me see you.

69
00:03:31,220 --> 00:03:32,500
What are you doing?

70
00:03:33,980 --> 00:03:34,740
Oh my god.

71
00:03:35,020 --> 00:03:36,340
Life is so unfair.

72
00:03:37,620 --> 00:03:38,420
How is it unfair?

73
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:39,100
Of course it is.

74
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:40,420
Look at you,
still so beautiful and thin.

75
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:40,940
Look at me.

76
00:03:41,380 --> 00:03:41,940
I've gotten so fat that...

77
00:03:42,020 --> 00:03:42,620
Look.

78
00:03:42,620 --> 00:03:44,980
What's wrong? You look gorgeous now.

79
00:03:44,980 --> 00:03:46,260
Let's not talk standing up. Sit down.

80
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:46,820
Come on.

81
00:03:46,820 --> 00:03:47,500
Okay.

82
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:47,900
I brought wine.

83
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:48,540
Come on.

84
00:03:48,620 --> 00:03:48,980
Okay.

85
00:03:49,140 --> 00:03:49,900
Come here.

86
00:03:50,460 --> 00:03:51,220
Have a seat.

87
00:03:51,220 --> 00:03:52,500
Isn't this the seat for paying the bill?

88
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:53,460
You won't be paying.

89
00:03:53,460 --> 00:03:54,980
Today, everything's on Wang Zeyuan.

90
00:03:57,860 --> 00:03:59,100
Listen, Tan Siting,

91
00:03:59,180 --> 00:04:00,580
I flew in on a full-price

92
00:04:00,580 --> 00:04:02,820
business class ticket
just to see you the moment

93
00:04:02,820 --> 00:04:03,300
you got back.

94
00:04:03,380 --> 00:04:03,780
Reimburse me.

95
00:04:04,020 --> 00:04:04,820
Fine, I will.

96
00:04:04,820 --> 00:04:05,260
I just got back

97
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:06,940
and Wang Shuhan already
scammed a fortune out of me.

98
00:04:07,740 --> 00:04:08,420
I'll cover it.

99
00:04:09,060 --> 00:04:10,060
Look at you, pathetic.

100
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:11,980
Come on, to celebrate Siting's return,

101
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:13,100
let's have a toast.

102
00:04:13,380 --> 00:04:13,860
Cheers!

103
00:04:19,620 --> 00:04:20,540
You finished it all?

104
00:04:20,860 --> 00:04:23,020
I'm really, really happy Siting is back.

105
00:04:23,300 --> 00:04:24,780
Another round?

106
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:26,140
Easy does it.

107
00:04:26,140 --> 00:04:26,900
If you drink too much,

108
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:28,140
you're gonna make a scene, right?

109
00:04:28,140 --> 00:04:31,020
Let me tell you, my alcohol tolerance
has improved over the years.

110
00:04:31,020 --> 00:04:32,500
It's not just your tolerance
that's grown.

111
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:33,540
Your weight has too.

112
00:04:34,860 --> 00:04:36,260
Do I need you to tell me that?

113
00:04:36,660 --> 00:04:37,940
It's obvious to everyone.

114
00:04:38,540 --> 00:04:39,500
If you tell anyone my weight

115
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:40,700
after leaving this room,

116
00:04:40,940 --> 00:04:41,540
I'll kill you.

117
00:04:43,780 --> 00:04:44,900
Let's drop this.
It's killing my appetite.

118
00:04:45,220 --> 00:04:45,740
Siting,

119
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:47,380
how was life over there for you?

120
00:04:48,140 --> 00:04:49,420
Pretty simple.

121
00:04:49,420 --> 00:04:50,660
A daily routine

122
00:04:50,780 --> 00:04:51,660
between the theater and home.

123
00:04:51,940 --> 00:04:54,140
Got to travel around sometimes
during tours.

124
00:04:57,740 --> 00:04:58,940
Zeyuan said

125
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:02,980
there's still no news
about your dad, right?

126
00:05:04,820 --> 00:05:05,300
Right.

127
00:05:06,700 --> 00:05:08,420
My dad doesn't have many relatives.

128
00:05:09,260 --> 00:05:10,540
Just a distant cousin.

129
00:05:11,620 --> 00:05:12,740
I contacted her.

130
00:05:13,300 --> 00:05:16,140
She said my dad hasn't reached out
to her all these years.

131
00:05:17,580 --> 00:05:19,460
I posted a missing person notice
for you online.

132
00:05:19,460 --> 00:05:21,580
If your dad
or anyone who knows him sees it,

133
00:05:21,860 --> 00:05:22,700
they'll contact us.

134
00:05:23,420 --> 00:05:23,900
Thank you.

135
00:05:24,300 --> 00:05:24,700
Right.

136
00:05:25,020 --> 00:05:27,300
Zeyuan is an expert
in that whole internet field.

137
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:28,660
He posted that notice.

138
00:05:28,660 --> 00:05:29,820
It's bound to help.

139
00:05:33,180 --> 00:05:33,940
Big changes, huh?

140
00:05:34,540 --> 00:05:35,100
Quite big.

141
00:05:35,740 --> 00:05:36,700
Have I changed much?

142
00:05:37,980 --> 00:05:38,540
Haven't I?

143
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:39,780
You've gotten more beautiful.

144
00:05:40,660 --> 00:05:41,500
Let me tell you,

145
00:05:42,220 --> 00:05:44,380
I never thought
I'd turn out like this either.

146
00:05:44,740 --> 00:05:45,740
And I never imagined

147
00:05:45,860 --> 00:05:47,860
I'd be living the life I have now.

148
00:05:48,780 --> 00:05:50,380
Shuhan, you know what?

149
00:05:51,220 --> 00:05:52,620
I've always envied you.

150
00:05:53,780 --> 00:05:54,500
Look,

151
00:05:56,340 --> 00:05:57,300
you have

152
00:05:58,220 --> 00:05:59,340
both your parents by your side.

153
00:06:00,180 --> 00:06:00,940
And

154
00:06:00,940 --> 00:06:03,060
you have such a thoughtful
and caring brother.

155
00:06:04,380 --> 00:06:05,220
Do you know

156
00:06:06,340 --> 00:06:07,540
how many years it's been

157
00:06:09,020 --> 00:06:10,260
since I last saw

158
00:06:10,940 --> 00:06:11,860
my dad?

159
00:06:14,660 --> 00:06:15,460
So,

160
00:06:15,860 --> 00:06:17,100
you should be content.

161
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:19,900
That's how you live happily.

162
00:06:20,980 --> 00:06:22,420
I am content.

163
00:06:23,180 --> 00:06:24,340
You envy me?

164
00:06:24,820 --> 00:06:25,980
I'm the one who envies you.

165
00:06:29,620 --> 00:06:30,780
Since you came back,

166
00:06:31,540 --> 00:06:32,700
have you seen that guy?

167
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:33,580
Who?

168
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:35,420
Don't play dumb.

169
00:06:37,620 --> 00:06:38,340
Feng Rui?

170
00:06:40,260 --> 00:06:40,780
Yes, I have.

171
00:06:41,580 --> 00:06:42,260
This afternoon.

172
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:44,740
So what's the deal with you two?

173
00:06:45,860 --> 00:06:46,540
Tell me.

174
00:06:46,660 --> 00:06:47,180
And

175
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:48,900
I heard he's not

176
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:50,660
at his grandfather's company anymore.

177
00:06:51,020 --> 00:06:52,980
Seems he started
his own winery or something.

178
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:55,980
The wine
you were downing earlier was his.

179
00:06:58,700 --> 00:06:59,860
I thought you brought it back

180
00:06:59,860 --> 00:07:01,140
from France for me.

181
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:03,940
With all that luggage,
you think I could carry wine?

182
00:07:04,180 --> 00:07:05,500
So who reached out to whom?

183
00:07:06,620 --> 00:07:08,380
No one reached out.

184
00:07:08,820 --> 00:07:11,620
I was just walking around this afternoon

185
00:07:12,380 --> 00:07:13,180
and happened to

186
00:07:14,220 --> 00:07:15,780
stumble into his winery.

187
00:07:16,620 --> 00:07:17,940
So we chatted for a bit.

188
00:07:21,380 --> 00:07:23,020
That's it?

189
00:07:23,740 --> 00:07:25,020
What else?

190
00:07:27,140 --> 00:07:29,340
You're not
rekindling old flames, are you?

191
00:07:29,340 --> 00:07:30,100
Enough.

192
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:31,180
What are you talking about?

193
00:07:31,660 --> 00:07:32,740
When I was about to leave,

194
00:07:32,740 --> 00:07:34,460
his wife and kid showed up.

195
00:07:34,820 --> 00:07:36,140
His kid is already this tall.

196
00:07:37,380 --> 00:07:38,300
Well, forget him then.

197
00:07:39,020 --> 00:07:40,180
You don't need him.

198
00:07:40,340 --> 00:07:41,500
I'll set you up.

199
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:42,620
I know tons of cute guys.

200
00:07:42,740 --> 00:07:43,620
All top-tier.

201
00:07:43,740 --> 00:07:45,460
You keep your top-tier guys.

202
00:07:45,460 --> 00:07:46,780
Gosh, you're incredibly confident.

203
00:07:46,940 --> 00:07:47,740
Top-tier?

204
00:07:47,740 --> 00:07:49,020
I'll introduce you to someone.

205
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:51,980
Otherwise, you'll be
all lonely back here.

206
00:07:51,980 --> 00:07:53,260
I'm not lonely.

207
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:54,180
For real.

208
00:07:54,180 --> 00:07:54,940
Alright.

209
00:08:04,220 --> 00:08:04,620
Grandma.

210
00:08:04,620 --> 00:08:05,260
Madam, you're here.

211
00:08:05,580 --> 00:08:05,900
Mom.

212
00:08:06,260 --> 00:08:06,900
Madam.

213
00:08:07,340 --> 00:08:08,340
Peiyan, you're here.

214
00:08:08,540 --> 00:08:09,220
You brought so many things.

215
00:08:09,220 --> 00:08:09,740
Let me.

216
00:08:09,740 --> 00:08:10,340
No, it's fine.

217
00:08:10,340 --> 00:08:11,020
Alright.

218
00:08:11,020 --> 00:08:11,300
What brings you here?

219
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:12,020
Come on.

220
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:12,780
Sit down.

221
00:08:12,780 --> 00:08:13,700
Have you eaten?

222
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:14,820
Would you like to join us?

223
00:08:14,900 --> 00:08:15,460
Don't bother.

224
00:08:15,540 --> 00:08:16,260
I've already eaten.

225
00:08:16,380 --> 00:08:16,820
Come here.

226
00:08:16,980 --> 00:08:17,740
Come on.

227
00:08:18,820 --> 00:08:20,060
This must be Peiyan's cooking?

228
00:08:20,860 --> 00:08:23,380
I just whipped up something simple
with what was in the fridge.

229
00:08:23,380 --> 00:08:24,420
It looks delicious.

230
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:24,980
Have some, Mom.

231
00:08:24,980 --> 00:08:25,460
Sit down.

232
00:08:25,580 --> 00:08:27,300
I've eaten. Sit down.

233
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:27,860
Peiyan,

234
00:08:27,860 --> 00:08:28,660
have a seat.

235
00:08:30,020 --> 00:08:30,900
Thank you.

236
00:08:31,260 --> 00:08:31,980
No problem.

237
00:08:31,980 --> 00:08:32,700
Next time,

238
00:08:32,740 --> 00:08:33,820
I'll get proper ingredients

239
00:08:33,940 --> 00:08:35,500
and make you
some of my specialty dishes.

240
00:08:35,860 --> 00:08:36,340
Okay.

241
00:08:39,380 --> 00:08:40,740
Grandma, what are you doing here?

242
00:08:40,740 --> 00:08:41,340
I...

243
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:46,860
Tomorrow's the weekend.

244
00:08:47,220 --> 00:08:48,900
Do you want to go to my place?

245
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:50,980
No.

246
00:08:50,980 --> 00:08:51,900
I haven't finished eating.

247
00:08:52,260 --> 00:08:53,620
And I still have homework.

248
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:58,060
I brought a game console.

249
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:00,140
I'm full now.

250
00:09:00,380 --> 00:09:01,140
Let's go. Game console.

251
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:03,100
Grab your homework.

252
00:09:03,100 --> 00:09:03,780
You didn't finish.

253
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:04,620
Let's go.

254
00:09:04,740 --> 00:09:06,060
Alright, we'll head out.

255
00:09:06,060 --> 00:09:07,180
I'm pretty much done, too.

256
00:09:07,180 --> 00:09:07,900
Don't bother.

257
00:09:08,060 --> 00:09:09,380
You two keep eating.

258
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:11,380
Be careful.

259
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:12,660
Got everything?

260
00:09:12,700 --> 00:09:13,140
Got it.

261
00:09:13,140 --> 00:09:13,500
I got everything.

262
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:14,900
Don't just play games.

263
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:16,100
You have piano lessons tomorrow.

264
00:09:16,140 --> 00:09:16,460
Okay.

265
00:09:17,260 --> 00:09:18,740
Don't worry. I'll do my homework
before playing games.

266
00:09:18,740 --> 00:09:19,660
Madam, let me see you out.

267
00:09:19,660 --> 00:09:20,060
It's fine.

268
00:09:20,380 --> 00:09:20,660
Don't bother.

269
00:09:20,660 --> 00:09:21,140
We'll walk you...

270
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:26,180
By the way,

271
00:09:26,580 --> 00:09:27,940
I'll bring him back tomorrow.

272
00:09:29,420 --> 00:09:30,060
Ma'am, bye...

273
00:09:35,860 --> 00:09:37,860
It's been a while
since you last visited me.

274
00:09:38,140 --> 00:09:39,020
Yeah.

275
00:09:39,220 --> 00:09:39,780
Lu.

276
00:09:40,020 --> 00:09:40,540
Put it here.

277
00:09:40,700 --> 00:09:41,260
Okay.

278
00:09:41,540 --> 00:09:43,180
Head back and get some rest.

279
00:09:43,620 --> 00:09:44,220
Alright, Ms. Gao.

280
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:45,980
I'll get going then.

281
00:09:45,980 --> 00:09:46,300
Okay.

282
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:46,740
Grandma.

283
00:09:46,740 --> 00:09:47,180
Bye, Ms. Gao.

284
00:09:47,540 --> 00:09:48,100
Close the door.

285
00:09:48,180 --> 00:09:48,660
Grandma?

286
00:09:49,740 --> 00:09:51,020
You haven't thrown away

287
00:09:51,020 --> 00:09:52,020
these old toys of mine?

288
00:09:52,780 --> 00:09:54,380
